---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import InfoBar from '../components/InfoBar.astro';
import '../styles/DescribedLink.css';
---

<Layout title="Amiah Belle Isle">
	<InfoBar />
	<main>
		<div>
			<h1>Professional Summary</h1>
			<p>&emsp; I am a senior computer science student with a strong focus on Java development. Through my coursework, which merited my inclusion on the dean's list, and my personal projects, I have developed a solid understanding of Java development. I am excited to contribute my skills to a Java development role and continue advancing in a professional environment.</p>
		</div>
		<div>
			<h1>Skills</h1>
			<ul>
				<li>Java</li>
				<li>Python</li>
				<li>C++</li>
				<li>Bash</li>
				<li>GitHub</li>
				<li>SQL</li>
				<li>JSON</li>
				<li>Teamwork</li>
				<li>Communication</li>
				<li>Familiar with Linux and Windows operating systems.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<div>
			<h1>Education</h1>
			<p>&emsp; Lakeland University, Wisconsin<br/>
			   &emsp; <b>Major: </b>Computer Science<br/>
			   &emsp; Expected to graduate 2025<br/></p>
		</div>
		<div>
			<h1>Projects</h1>

			{/*This website*/}
			<div class="described-link">
				<div class="dl-title">
			
				<a href="https://github.com/AmiahBelleIsle/hardware-spec-get">Hardware Specification Getter<img style="display: inline; padding-left: 0.4rem; vertical-align:sub" src="../external-link-simple-pink.svg" /></a>
			
				<p>Java</p>
			
				</div>
				<div class="dl-content">
				<p>A JavaFX application to display hardware specifications in an interactive GUI. Utilizes OSHI for hardware data collection and Jackson for JSON file management. Features include customizable image display and the ability to reorder or disable hardware information entries. Dependencies are managed with Maven.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			{/*Python Noise Gen*/}
			<div class="described-link">
				<div class="dl-title">
			
				<a href="https://github.com/AmiahBelleIsle/python_noise_generator">Image Noise Generator <img style="display: inline; padding-left: 0.2rem; vertical-align:sub" src="../external-link-simple-pink.svg" /></a>
			
				<p>Python</p>
			
				</div>
				<div class="dl-content">
				<p>A Python application using Tkinter and PIL for image noise generation. Features include a resizable canvas, grayscale option, seed input for custom noise patterns, and the ability to save generated images for external use.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			{/*Bash ff apt*/}
			<div class="described-link">
				<div class="dl-title">
			
				<a href="https://github.com/AmiahBelleIsle/apt-install-firefox-script">Automated Debian Firefox Install Script<img style="display: inline; padding-left: 0.4rem; vertical-align:sub" src="../external-link-simple-pink.svg" /></a>
			
				<p>Bash</p>
			
				</div>
				<div class="dl-content">
				<p>This shell script installs Firefox on Debian based systems using apt. It automatically imports the Mozilla signing key and pins the .deb version, which resolves dependency errors that may happen otherwise.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
  
		</div>

	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		margin: auto;
		padding: 1rem;
		width: fit-content;
		max-width: calc(100% - 2rem);
		color: #f9d8d2;
		font-size: large;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	ul {
		list-style-type:disc;
		display:flex;
		flex-direction: row;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}
	ul li {
		margin-right: 2rem;
	}
	h1::after {
		content: "";
		position:absolute;
		display: block;
		background: linear-gradient(90deg,#f9d8d2 66%,  #121738);
		border-radius: 5%;
		height: 5px;
		width: calc(95% - 2rem);
	}
	{/*Desktop Styling*/}
	@media (min-width: 769px){
		main {
			margin: 0;
			margin-left: 30.5vw;
			margin-right: 10vw;
			width: fit-content;
		}
		h1::after {
			width: calc(55% - 2rem);
		}
	}
	
</style>
